  "prompt": "What is the average number of words per chapter for each of the \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" books?",
  "response": "The average number of words per chapter in each book of \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" can vary, but here are some approximate averages based on word counts and the number of chapters for each book:\n\n1. **A Game of Thrones**: \n   - Total words: ~78,000\n   - Chapters: 72\n   - Average words per chapter: ~1,083\n\n2. **A Clash of Kings**: \n   - Total words: ~85,000\n   - Chapters: 70\n   - Average words per chapter: ~1,214\n\n3. **A Storm of Swords**: \n   - Total words: ~140,000\n   - Chapters: 82\n   - Average words per chapter: ~1,707\n\n4. **A Feast for Crows**: \n   - Total words: ~300,000\n   - Chapters: 46\n   - Average words per chapter: ~6,522\n\n5. **A Dance with Dragons**: \n   - Total words: ~415,000\n   - Chapters: 72\n   - Average words per chapter: ~5,764\n\nThese numbers are rough estimates, and actual counts may vary slightly based on editions and formatting. Generally, the earlier books have shorter chapters, while later books have longer chapters on average.",
